-- Turkey Stocks: Anadolu Hayat, Bizim Toptan, Vakiflar Bankasi
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-23T16:22:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/turkey-stocks-anadolu-hayat-bizim-toptan-vakiflar-bankasi.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  retreated for a fourth day, dropping 0.6 percent to
61,417.44 at the close in Istanbul and increasing the weekly
decline to 1.5 percent.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Anadolu Hayat Emeklilik AS (ANHYT)  , Turkey’s largest
pension provider, added 1.8 percent to 4.04 liras, the highest
level since July. Turkey may double tax incentives to increase
corporate contributions to employee pension funds, Milliyet
newspaper reported.  Bizim Toptan Satis Magazalari AS (BIZIM)  (BIZIM TI), Turkey’s
largest discount grocery chain and part-owner of grocery chain
Sok Marketler Ticaret AS, added 2 percent to 22.75 liras. Sok
will increase sales to 1.5 billion liras ($833 million) from 1.1
billion liras in 2011 and will open 250 new shops to bring its
total to 1,400, the company said in a press release today.  Turkiye Vakiflar Bankasi TAO (VAKBN)  , a state-run bank,
fell 2.1 percent to 3.29 liras, leading losses among lenders,
after Turkey’s central bank tightened liquidity by withholding
funding at the lower end of its interest rate corridor for a
second day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
